cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the development of a computational model for small target motion detection. Additionally, the use of visual features and motion-sensitive neurons also suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The integration of motion information to filter out false positives may also involve machine learning techniques, which could place this paper in the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the potential applications of this model in searching and tracking suggest a connection to robotics (cs.RO) sub-category.
